cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a framework for designing real-time convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for vision tasks such as face detection, gender classification, and emotion classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of regularization methods and visualization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The deployment of the system on a robot suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of pre-trained architectures and the release of code and demos suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
